==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Haricot
<hw>Har"i*cot</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧r"⟦esl⟧*k⟦osl⟧; F.
⟦adot⟧`r⟦esl⟧`k⟦osl⟧")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A ragout or stew of meat with beans and other vegetables.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The ripe seeds, or the unripe pod, of the common
string bean (<spn>Phaseolus vulgaris</spn>), used as a vegetable. Other
species of the same genus furnish different kinds of haricots.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Harier</ent>⟦br⟧
